    "Roboflow is more of a platform for managing and pre-processing image datasets, while the Albumentations library is specifically focused on image augmentation for machine learning.",
    "Since our dataset comprises different quality images (Mars and Lunar), the model is trained for various image qualities.",
    "Due to this our model can be tested by any quality of image.",
    "Figure 4a is the original image of the Moon surface from the Mars_Lunar Dataset.",
    "Figure 1b presents the labeled feature using Roboflow, the X and Y-axis are the pixel values of the image where each pixel is 0.5-2 m. A dataset of 2000 TMC 2 images has been annotated with crater locations and sizes by human experts and is currently used for training and testing crater detection algorithms."
